An analysis of the MUC-3 evaluation suggests that all of the MUC-3 systems experienced significant difficulty with relevant text classification (Krupka et al.1991). Although some texts will inevitably require in-depth natural language understanding capabilities in order to be correctly classified, we will demonstrate that skimming techniques can be used to identify subsets of a corpus that can be classified with very high levels of precision.
